article.headline: Clemson 90, S. Carolina St. 63
article.story: CLEMSON, S.C. -- K.C. Rivers scored 19 points and Trevor Booker added 18 to lead Clemson to a 90-63 victory over South Carolina State on Saturday. The win marked the fourth straight season the Tigers (10-0)won their first 10 games. Clemson led by 24 points at halftime and by many as 30 in the second half. David Potter's 3-pointer gave the Tigers a 66-36 advantage with 11:25 left in the second half, as the Bulldogs (5-4) never got closer than 23 points the rest of the way. Jason Flagler scored 17 points to lead the Bulldogs and Wesley Telfare added 13 points. Terrence Oglesby hit four 3-pointers in less five minutes as the Tigers expanded an early 18-15 lead to 33-17. Oglesby finished with 14 points. Led by Oglesby and Rivers, the Tigers pulled out to a 47-23 halftime advantage.
